{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860350136,"sessionID":"ses_28679d8d7ffeBD6ezRS0zvKUr1","part":{"id":"prt_d79867c86001qOUrvFidT780ZN","messageID":"msg_d79866e7f001WVt935MrwQnOdR","sessionID":"ses_28679d8d7ffeBD6ezRS0zvKUr1","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_tool-6cd7a157f4994bc0ba10687501a51f73","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"AR-016","path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z"},"output":"Found 14 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016 Implementation Summary\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016 Implementation Plan\n  Line 3: **Feature:** AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n  Line 1761: This implementation plan breaks down AR-016 (PicoD 文件管理 API) into 8 atomic, independently verifiable tasks:\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md:\n  Line 3: ## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n  Line 11: PicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n  Line 44: changes/AR-016/\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016 Delta Specification: PicoD 文件管理 API\n  Line 11: - proposal.md: AR-016 提案文档，概述 PicoD 文件管理 API 的目的、范围、设计和实现策略\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016: PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/README.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016 Implementation Notes\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/CHANGE.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n  Line 4: - **AR**: AR-016","metadata":{"matches":14,"truncated":false},"title":"AR-016","time":{"start":1775860350121,"end":1775860350135}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860350146,"sessionID":"ses_28679d8d7ffeBD6ezRS0zvKUr1","part":{"id":"prt_d79867a78001Fkuug0zlpfdQpl","messageID":"msg_d79866e7f001WVt935MrwQnOdR","sessionID":"ses_28679d8d7ffeBD6ezRS0zvKUr1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-62dcb19ac399492ea2ea557277441b6e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: **Feature:** AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n4: **Goal:** 实现完整的文件管理 API，包括文件上传、下载、列表查询、删除、目录创建和元数据查询，提供安全的文件操作能力。\n5: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n6: - DELETE /api/files/*path 支持文件和目录删除，包括递归删除\n7: - PUT /api/files/*path 支持目录创建，包括递归创建\n8: - GET /api/files/*path 支持通过 metadata=true 参数获取详细文件元数据\n9: - GET /api/files 支持通过 recursive 参数递归列出目录内容\n10: - 所有路径操作都经过严格的安全验证（工作空间监狱）\n11: - 实现文件操作锁，防止并发写入冲突\n12: - 所有端点返回统一的 JSON 错误响应格式\n13: - 单元测试覆盖率 >90%\n14: - 集成测试覆盖所有 API 端点\n15: **Architecture:** RESTful API 设计，基于 Gin 框架，JWT 认证保护所有端点，路径安全验证确保工作空间隔离。\n16: **Tech Stack:** Go 1.25, Gin, JWT, 标准库文件操作\n17: **前端验证:** No\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Task 1: Add DELETE handler for file/directory deletion\n22: \n23: **Files:**\n24: - Modify: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n25: - Modify: `pkg/picod/handlers.go`\n26: - Modify: `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n27: - Modify: `pkg/picod/constants.go`\n28: \n29: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n30: \n31: ```go\n32: // pkg/picod/handlers_test.go\n33: package picod\n34: \n35: import (\n36: \t\"net/http\"\n37: \t\"net/http/httptest\"\n38: \t\"os\"\n39: \t\"path/filepath\"\n40: \t\"strings\"\n41: \t\"testing\"\n42: \n43: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n44: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n45: )\n46: \n47: func TestDeleteFileHandler(t *testing.T) {\n48: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n49: \n50: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n51: \trouter := gin.New()\n52: \n53: \ttempDir := t.TempDir()\n54: \tserver := &Server{\n55: \t\tworkspaceDir: tempDir,\n56: \t\tauthManager:  nil, // Skip auth for tests\n57: \t}\n58: \n59: \trouter.DELETE(\"/api/files/*path\", server.DeleteFileHandler)\n60: \n61: \t// Create a test file\n62: \ttestFile := filepath.Join(tempDir, \"test.txt\")\n63: \tif err := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644); err != nil {\n64: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create test file: %v\", err)\n65: \t}\n66: \n67: \t// Test deleting a file\n68: \treq, _ := http.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", \"/api/files/test.txt\", nil)\n69: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n70: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n71: \n72: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n73: \n74: \t// Verify file was deleted\n75: \t_, err := os.Stat(testFile)\n76: \tg.Expect(os.IsNotExist(err)).To(BeTrue())\n77: \n78: \t// Test deleting non-existent file\n79: \treq, _ = http.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", \"/api/files/nonexistent.txt\", nil)\n80: \tw = httptest.NewRecorder()\n81: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n82: \n83: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusNotFound))\n84: }\n85: \n86: func TestDeleteDirectoryHandler(t *testing.T) {\n87: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n88: \n89: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n90: \trouter := gin.New()\n91: \n92: \ttempDir := t.TempDir()\n93: \tserver := &Server{\n94: \t\tworkspaceDir: tempDir,\n95: \t\tauthManager:  nil,\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \trouter.DELETE(\"/api/files/*path\", server.DeleteFileHandler)\n99: \n100: \t// Create a test directory with files\n101: \ttestDir := filepath.Join(tempDir, \"testdir\")\n102: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(testDir, 0755); err != nil {\n103: \t\tt.Fatalf(\"Failed to create test directory: %v\", err)\n104: \t}\n105: \ttestFile := filepath.Join(testDir, \"file.txt\")\n106: \tos.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"content\"), 0644)\n107: \n108: \t// Test deleting non-empty directory without recursive flag\n109: \treq, _ := http.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", \"/api/files/testdir?recursive=false\", nil)\n110: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n111: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n112: \n113: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusBadRequest))\n114: \n115: \t// Test deleting non-empty directory with recursive flag\n116: \treq, _ = http.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", \"/api/files/testdir?recursive=true\", nil)\n117: \tw = httptest.NewRecorder()\n118: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n119: \n120: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n121: \n122: \t// Verify directory was deleted\n123: \t_, err := os.Stat(testDir)\n124: \tg.Expect(os.IsNotExist(err)).To(BeTrue())\n125: }\n126: ```\n127: \n128: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n129: \n130: Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/ -run TestDeleteFileHandler -v`\n131: Expected: FAIL with \"undefined: DeleteFileHandler\"\n132: \n133: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: // pkg/picod/constants.go\n137: const (\n138: \t// Add new error messages\n139: \tErrMsgDirectoryNotEmpty = \"Directory not empty, use recursive=true to delete\"\n140: \tErrPathAlreadyExists    = \"Path already exists\"\n141: )\n142: \n143: // pkg/picod/errors.go\n144: const (\n145: \tErrDirectoryNotEmpty = \"DirectoryNotEmpty\"\n146: \tErrPathAlreadyExists = \"PathAlreadyExists\"\n147: )\n148: \n149: var statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n150: \t// ... existing entries ...\n151: \tErrDirectoryNotEmpty: http.StatusBadRequest,\n152: \tErrPathAlreadyExists: http.StatusConflict,\n153: }\n154: \n155: // pkg/picod/handlers.go\n156: func (s *Server) DeleteFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n157: \tpath := c.Param(\"path\")\n158: \tif path == \"\" {\n159: \t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrMissingPath, ErrMsgMissingPathParam, \"\", nil))\n160: \t\treturn\n161: \t}\n162: \n163: \tpath = strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")\n164: \n165: \tsanitizedPath, err := s.sanitizePath(path)\n166: \tif err != nil {\n167: \t\tHandleError(c, err)\n168: \t\treturn\n169: \t}\n170: \n171: \tinfo, err := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n172: \tif err != nil {\n173: \t\tif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n174: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrFileNotFound, ErrMsgFileNotFound, \"\", err))\n175: \t\t} else {\n176: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to get file info\", err.Error(), err))\n177: \t\t}\n178: \t\treturn\n179: \t}\n180: \n181: \trecursive := c.Query(\"recursive\") == \"true\"\n182: \n183: \tif info.IsDir() {\n184: \t\t// Check if directory is empty\n185: \t\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)\n186: \t\tif err != nil {\n187: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to read directory\", err.Error(), err))\n188: \t\t\treturn\n189: \t\t}\n190: \n191: \t\tif len(entries) > 0 && !recursive {\n192: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrDirectoryNotEmpty, ErrMsgDirectoryNotEmpty, \"\", nil))\n193: \t\t\treturn\n194: \t\t}\n195: \n196: \t\tif err := os.RemoveAll(sanitizedPath); err != nil {\n197: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to delete directory\", err.Error(), err))\n198: \t\t\treturn\n199: \t\t}\n200: \t} else {\n201: \t\tif err := os.Remove(sanitizedPath); err != nil {\n202: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to delete file\", err.Error(), err))\n203: \t\t\treturn\n204: \t\t}\n205: \t}\n206: \n207: \tklog.Infof(\"Deleted path: %s (recursive: %v)\", sanitizedPath, recursive)\n208: \n209: \tresponse := DeleteFileResponse{\n210: \t\tPath:    path,\n211: \t\tDeleted: true,\n212: \t}\n213: \n214: \tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, response)\n215: }\n216: \n217: // pkg/picod/files.go\n218: type DeleteFileResponse struct {\n219: \tPath    string `json:\"path\"`\n220: \tDeleted bool   `json:\"deleted\"`\n221: }\n222: ```\n223: \n224: **Step 4: Register the route in server.go**\n225: \n226: ```go\n227: // pkg/picod/server.go\n228: func (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n229: \tapi := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n230: \tapi.Use(AuthMiddleware(s.authManager))\n231: \t{\n232: \t\tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n233: \t\tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n234: \t\tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n235: \t\tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n236: \t\tapi.DELETE(\"/files/*path\", s.DeleteFileHandler) // Add this line\n237: \t}\n238: \n239: \ts.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: **Step 5: Run test to verify it passes**\n244: \n245: Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/ -run TestDeleteFileHandler -v`\n246: Expected: PASS\n247: \n248: **Step 6: Commit**\n249: \n250: ```bash\n251: git add pkg/picod/server.go pkg/picod/handlers.go pkg/picod/errors.go pkg/picod/constants.go pkg/picod/files.go pkg/picod/handlers_test.go\n252: git commit -m \"feat(ar-016): add DELETE handler for file/directory deletion\"\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ### Task 2: Add PUT handler for directory creation\n258: \n259: **Files:**\n260: - Modify: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n261: - Modify: `pkg/picod/handlers.go`\n262: - Modify: `pkg/picod/files.go`\n263: \n264: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n265: \n266: ```go\n267: // pkg/picod/handlers_test.go\n268: func TestCreateDirectoryHandler(t *testing.T) {\n269: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n270: \n271: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n272: \trouter := gin.New()\n273: \n274: \ttempDir := t.TempDir()\n275: \tserver := &Server{\n276: \t\tworkspaceDir: tempDir,\n277: \t\tauthManager:  nil,\n278: \t}\n279: \n280: \trouter.PUT(\"/api/files/*path\", server.CreateDirectoryHandler)\n281: \n282: \t// Test creating a single directory\n283: \treq, _ := http.NewRequest(\"PUT\", \"/api/files/newdir?mode=0755\", nil)\n284: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n285: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n286: \n287: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n288: \n289: \t// Verify directory was created\n290: \tdirPath := filepath.Join(tempDir, \"newdir\")\n291: \tinfo, err := os.Stat(dirPath)\n292: \tg.Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n293: \tg.Expect(info.IsDir()).To(BeTrue())\n294: \n295: \t// Test creating nested directories with recursive=true\n296: \treq, _ = http.NewRequest(\"PUT\", \"/api/files/parent/child?recursive=true\", nil)\n297: \tw = httptest.NewRecorder()\n298: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n299: \n300: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n301: \n302: \tnestedPath := filepath.Join(tempDir, \"parent\", \"child\")\n303: \tinfo, err = os.Stat(nestedPath)\n304: \tg.Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n305: \tg.Expect(info.IsDir()).To(BeTrue())\n306: \n307: \t// Test creating directory that already exists\n308: \treq, _ = http.NewRequest(\"PUT\", \"/api/files/newdir\", nil)\n309: \tw = httptest.NewRecorder()\n310: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n311: \n312: \tg.Expect(w.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusConflict))\n313: }\n314: ```\n315: \n316: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n317: \n318: Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/ -run TestCreateDirectoryHandler -v`\n319: Expected: FAIL with \"undefined: CreateDirectoryHandler\"\n320: \n321: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n322: \n323: ```go\n324: // pkg/picod/handlers.go\n325: func (s *Server) CreateDirectoryHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n326: \tpath := c.Param(\"path\")\n327: \tif path == \"\" {\n328: \t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrMissingPath, ErrMsgMissingPathParam, \"\", nil))\n329: \t\treturn\n330: \t}\n331: \n332: \tpath = strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")\n333: \n334: \tsanitizedPath, err := s.sanitizePath(path)\n335: \tif err != nil {\n336: \t\tHandleError(c, err)\n337: \t\treturn\n338: \t}\n339: \n340: \t// Check if path already exists\n341: \tinfo, err := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n342: \tif err == nil {\n343: \t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrPathAlreadyExists, ErrMsgPathAlreadyExists, \"\", nil))\n344: \t\treturn\n345: \t}\n346: \n347: \tmodeStr := c.Query(\"mode\")\n348: \tmode := parseFileMode(modeStr)\n349: \tif mode == DefaultFileMode {\n350: \t\tmode = DefaultDirMode\n351: \t}\n352: \n353: \trecursive := c.Query(\"recursive\") != \"false\" // Default to true\n354: \n355: \tif recursive {\n356: \t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(sanitizedPath, mode); err != nil {\n357: \t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to c